From: Gunnar Hjalmarsson <gunnarhj@ubuntu.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Jul 2024 19:42:55 -0400
Subject: Don't fetch remote images when reading docs on disk

This fixes a privacy breach previously reported as Lintian warnings
(privacy-breach-generic): README.md embeds remote CI-badge and logo
images that get fetched when the file is rendered outside of GitHub,
e.g. by tools that turn packaged docs into HTML.

Rebased for opencc 1.4.0: README.md has grown more remote badges since
this patch was first written, so all of them plus the logo image are
dropped here.

Forwarded: not-needed
Reviewed-by: xiao sheng wen <atzlinux@debian.org>
Last-Update: 2026-07-04
---
--- a/README.md	2026-07-04 01:16:39.390649630 +0000
+++ b/README.md	2026-07-04 01:16:50.939855014 +0000
@@ -1,23 +1,7 @@
